===subject:Chap 4
===from:Chris Comer
===date:Tue Feb 18 11:32:01 2003
===message:
With or with out the war slavery would have ended. I think slavery would end even with no change in basic attitude on the part of pro-slavery Americans, toward slavery I mean. The reason is pure economics. By the 1860’s the rest of the “modern” world had abandoned slavery and found it to be unsavory. The economic pressure and probable trade sanctions brought on the US by the rest of the world would have forced a change. We are a capitalist nation and the planters were also capitalist. They did not keep slaves for entertainment but because they were profitable. As technology marched forward machines would have become more profitable than slaves, who have to be feed sheltered and clothed.  This may not be the most compassionate scenario but I don’t think that it is too far off the mark. Of course I would hope that a change of heart would have happened on the part of the planters.

=========yorg=========
